The paper deals with the problem of recovering low rank matrices corrupted by sparse outliers, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. The proposed solution involves updating the principal directions of the low rank part in real-time, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves solving a compressive sensing type problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a solution that utilizes time correlation models, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA) or signal processing (cs.SI).
